.TH "blk_ksm_init" 9 "blk_ksm_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_ksm_init \- Initialize a keyslot manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" blk_ksm_init
.BI "(struct blk_keyslot_manager *ksm "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_slots "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ksm" 12
The keyslot_manager to initialize.
.IP "num_slots" 12
The number of key slots to manage.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate memory for keyslots and initialize a keyslot manager. Called by
e.g. storage drivers to set up a keyslot manager in their request_queue.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or else a negative error code.
